    "text": {
      "*": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p><b><a href=\"/Main_Page\" title=\"Main Page\">Home</a> * <a href=\"/People\" title=\"People\">People</a> * Arkadiusz Paterek</b>\n</p>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:200px;\"><a href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/in/paterek/\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/c/c7/ArkadiuszPaterek.jpg\" width=\"198\" height=\"198\" class=\"thumbimage\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/File:ArkadiuszPaterek.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Arkadiusz Paterek <sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></div></div></div> \n<p><b>Arkadiusz Paterek</b>,<br />\na Polish computer and data scientist with interests in <a href=\"/Programming\" title=\"Programming\">programming</a>, <a href=\"/Learning\" title=\"Learning\">machine learning</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Recommender_system\">recommender system</a> and <a href=\"/Deep_Learning\" title=\"Deep Learning\">deep learning</a> <sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>, and chess player <sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>. \nHe holds a masters degree from <a href=\"/University_of_Warsaw\" title=\"University of Warsaw\">University of Warsaw</a>, with a thesis entitled <i>Modeling of an evaluation function in chess</i> <sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>, \nelaborating on the <a href=\"/Neural_Networks#Perceptron\" title=\"Neural Networks\">single-layer perceptron</a> design of an <a href=\"/Evaluation_Function\" title=\"Evaluation Function\">evaluation function</a>.\nInspired by <a href=\"/Michael_Buro\" title=\"Michael Buro\">Michael Buro's</a> <a href=\"/Michael_Buro#GLEM\" title=\"Michael Buro\">GLEM</a> approach <sup id=\"cite_ref-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup> in the domain of <a href=\"/Othello\" title=\"Othello\">Othello</a>, Arkadiusz Paterek used his own chess program <a href=\"/Gosu\" title=\"Gosu\">Gosu</a>, \nto <a href=\"/Automated_Tuning\" title=\"Automated Tuning\">tune</a> its evaluation by <a href=\"/Automated_Tuning#LogisticRegression\" title=\"Automated Tuning\">logistic regression</a>.\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Selected_Publications\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Selected Publications</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Forum_Posts\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Forum Posts</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#External_Links\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">External Links</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Selected_Publications\">Selected Publications</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Arkadiusz_Paterek&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Selected Publications\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<p><sup id=\"cite_ref-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<ul><li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Arkadiusz Paterek</a> (<b>2004</b>). <i>Modelowanie funkcji oceniającej w szachach</i>. Masters thesis, <a href=\"/University_of_Warsaw\" title=\"University of Warsaw\">University of Warsaw</a> (Polish, Modeling of an evaluation function in chess)</li>\n<li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Arkadiusz Paterek</a> (<b>2004</b>). <i>Modelowanie funkcji oceniającej w grach</i>. <a href=\"/University_of_Warsaw\" title=\"University of Warsaw\">University of Warsaw</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.mimuw.edu.pl/~paterek/mfog.ps.gz\">zipped ps</a> (Polish, Modeling of an evaluation function in games)</li>\n<li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Arkadiusz Paterek</a> (<b>2007</b>). <i>Improving regularized singular value decomposition for collaborative filtering</i>. KDD Cup and Workshop 2007, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://arek-paterek.com/ap_kdd.pdf\">pdf</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.mimuw.edu.pl/~paterek/ap_kdd.pdf\">pdf</a> <sup id=\"cite_ref-7\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup> <sup id=\"cite_ref-8\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Arkadiusz Paterek</a> (<b>2012</b>). <i>Predicting movie ratings and recommender systems</i>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://arek-paterek.com/predict.pdf\">pdf</a></li></ul>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Forum_Posts\">Forum Posts</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Arkadiusz_Paterek&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Forum Posts\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<ul><li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://w.open-aurec.com/wbforum/viewtopic.php?f=18&amp;t=48980\">gosu v.0.2</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Arek Paterek</a>, <a href=\"/Computer_Chess_Forums\" title=\"Computer Chess Forums\">Winboard Forum</a>, September 20, 2004</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://w.open-aurec.com/wbforum/viewtopic.php?f=2&amp;t=127#p327\">Re: Gosu does not find the mate in 1...</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Arek Paterek</a>, <a href=\"/Computer_Chess_Forums\" title=\"Computer Chess Forums\">Winboard Forum</a>, October 03, 2004</li></ul>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"External_Links\">External Links</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Arkadiusz_Paterek&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: External Links\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<ul><li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://arek-paterek.com/\">Arkadiusz Paterek - homepage</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/in/paterek/\">Arkadiusz Paterek - Polska | LinkedIn</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.chessgames.com/perl/chessplayer?pid=92667\">The chess games of Arkadiusz Paterek</a> from <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.chessgames.com/index.html\">chessgames.com</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.365chess.com/players/Arkadiusz_Paterek\">Arkadiusz Paterek chess games - 365Chess.com</a></li></ul>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Arkadiusz_Paterek&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/in/paterek/\">Arkadiusz Paterek - Polska | LinkedIn</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://arek-paterek.com/\">Arkadiusz Paterek's Homepage</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-3\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.szachypolskie.pl/katarzyna-kucharska/\">Katarzyna Kucharska - Szachy w Polsce</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-4\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Arkadiusz Paterek</a> (<b>2004</b>). <i>Modelowanie funkcji oceniającej w szachach</i>. Masters thesis, <a href=\"/University_of_Warsaw\" title=\"University of Warsaw\">University of Warsaw</a> (Polish, Modeling of the evaluation function in chess)</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-5\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-5\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"> <a href=\"/Michael_Buro\" title=\"Michael Buro\">Michael Buro</a> (<b>1998</b>). <i><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://link.springer.com/chapter/10.1007/3-540-48957-6_8\">From Simple Features to Sophisticated Evaluation Functions</a></i>. <a href=\"/CG_1998\" title=\"CG 1998\">CG 1998</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://skatgame.net/mburo/ps/glem.pdf\">pdf</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-6\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-6\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://scholar.google.com/citations?user=PKa5IYAAAAAJ&amp;hl=en\">Arkadiusz Paterek - Google Scholar Citations</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-7\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-7\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Collaborative_filtering\">Collaborative filtering from Wikipedia</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-8\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-8\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Netflix_Prize\">Netflix Prize from Wikipedia</a></span>\n</li>\n</ol></div> \n<p><b><a href=\"/People\" title=\"People\">Up one level</a></b>\n</p>\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nCached time: 20260301081205\nCache expiry: 86400\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.019 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.021 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 131/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 294/1000000\nPost‐expand include size: 0/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 0/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 2/40\nExpensive parser function count: 0/100\n-->\n<!--\nTransclusion expansion time report (%,ms,calls,template)\n100.00%    0.000      1 -total\n-->\n</div>\n<!-- Saved in parser cache with key oscar70_mw1-mw_:pcache:idhash:5405-0!canonical and timestamp 20260301081205 and revision id 11521\n -->\n"
